# Satellite General Conventions

Apply these conventions to all changes in this repository.

## Naming Conventions
- Use `satellite_<resource_plural>` for top-level data lists.
- Use `satellite_<domain>.yaml` for dispatch task files.
- Use `get_<domain>.yaml` for filetree export task files.
- Use `satellite_<resource>.d/` for filetree fragment directories.
- Use `__` prefix for temporary loop/internal variables (example: `__current_repository`).

## FQCN Rules
- Always use `ansible.builtin.*` for builtin modules and task includes.
- Always use `redhat.satellite.*` for Satellite resources and helper modules.
- Prefer `redhat.satellite` roles via `ansible.builtin.import_role` when available; otherwise use `redhat.satellite.*` modules.
- Use `ansible.builtin.uri` only when no `redhat.satellite` role/module is available for that operation.
- Use `infra.satellite_configuration.*` for this collection's roles/modules.
- Do not introduce new `theforeman.foreman.*` tasks.

## Task Style
- Prefer loops over `satellite_*` lists, not duplicated one-off tasks.
- Use `| default(omit)` for optional module parameters.
- Delegate Satellite API operations to `localhost` when appropriate.
- Keep changes idempotent and data-driven.

## Cross-Role Consistency Rule
- When adding a new object type, update all three roles in the same change:
  - `roles/filetree_create` (export)
  - `roles/filetree_read` (ingest)
  - `roles/dispatch` (apply)
- Add matching tags and naming across the three roles for the same object type.
- Do not add partial support for a new object type in only one role.
